<br>
I cannot speak for every single member of Triality, but I know that at least the huge majority of us would love to just ignore AD.  My question is HOW can we go about doing this?  People who say things like &quot;just get better at what you do and beat them to the mobs&quot; or &quot;just pretend they're not there and kill what you want&quot; are missing the point.  We DO beat them to mobs (e.g. we killed the Vindi and Statue last night), but then they get a GM to come and award them whatever they want to kill.  If we ignore them and run them over, they either train us or get a GM to come rescue them.  If your advice is to just ignore AD, can you explain how that can be done?  Do we wait until we are engaged with Statue and then just &quot;/rs everyone ignore those 12 giants and that Feign Death'd Kandom in our camp.  If those giants are beating on you, be a man.  Just ignore them.&quot;  When the GM says &quot;/shout all Triality people leave this zone now.  AD has decided that they want to raid here, so the zone is now theirs&quot;, do we just keep pulling to our target and kill it?  I'm not clear on the logistics of the /ignore AD strategy.<br>
<br>
The simple fact is that ignoring AD and doing your own things has not worked and we have tried.  Even if we win, we cannot win.  They will find a way to rob us using whatever means they need...training, leapfrogging, luring Amato to their aid with the promise of twinkies, etc.<br>
<br>
Triality does not want to fight AD by resorting to thier tactics.  Therefore, it seems like our only recourse is to take away the Emp from them.<br>
<br>
One last thing.  To suggest that Triality should just let AD have the Emporer and whatever else it wants so that they can move on and be out of our way shows a complete lack of understanding regarding AD.  These fuckers are not ever going to move on at an acceptable rate.  They have been doing AoW since we started with our first farming of Vindi BP's and ST keys.  As we are winding down to where we only expect 2 or 3 more AoW kills to be done with him, AD is now moving backwards in content to trying to farm NToV for their new legion of ex-Fantasy gimps (gogogo Zerg Force Restock!)  If we stop all raids and let AD just have NtoV, AoW, AL, HP, Burrower, ST, Tunare, Shei, and whatever else they want until they are finally ready to move on to VT, then we will get to go through all of this again in another month when we again catch up to AD.  Conceding every mob to AD to get them out of the way would only make sense if they had competent leadership that we felt would then move their guild forward at a reasonable pace. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=shylahsoulshine>Shylah Soulshine</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pally Puff Girl</span><br>  Posts: 781<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/8/03 2:07:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2021.topic&index=33>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Agree</span><hr size=1> cockblocking is a retarded idea no matter what. why waste time blocking them on a mob when you can be killing some other mob and getting your guild loots?<br>
